Mxolisi Mngadi, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; KwaZulu-Natal police have launched a manhunt for a serial rapist who apparently lures unsuspecting victims with the promise of employment.Police said the man had been operating in Westville, west of Durban.Westville police said on Tuesday that they were investigating eight cases of rape, where the rapist used the same modus operandi."We cannot divulge further information at this stage since the cases are still under investigation," Captain Nqobile Gwala said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.